OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773864688
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FWhat is meningitis and who can it
OL,7,Faffect?
OL,9,FMeningitis is inflammation of the
OL,10,Fmembranes that surround the brain and
OL,11,Fspinal cord. It can be caused by
OL,12,Fviruses or bacteria, but the most
OL,13,Fserious cases are often caused by the
OL,14,Fbacterium Neisseria meningitidis.
OL,16,FAnyone can get meningitis, but it is
OL,17,Fmost commonly caught by babies, young
OL,18,Fchildren, teenagers and young adults.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/25
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773864688
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FThis is due in part to people in this
OL,7,Fage group carrying the bacteria in the
OL,8,Fnose or throat without symptoms.
OL,10,FThe bacteria that cause meningococcal
OL,11,Fmeningitis are often carried
OL,12,Fharmlessly in the nose and throat;
OL,13,Faround 10% of the general population
OL,14,Fcarries them without ever becoming
OL,15,Fill. In adolescents and young adults,
OL,16,Fcarriage can be higher, with large UK
OL,17,Fstudies showing rates between 7% and
OL,18,F18%.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/25
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773864688
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FTransmission requires close, prolonged
OL,7,Fcontact such as coughing, sneezing or
OL,8,Fkissing, and even among carriers only
OL,9,Fa very small proportion ever develops
OL,10,Finvasive disease.
OL,12,FOutbreaks usually happen when a
OL,13,Fparticular meningococcal strain enters
OL,14,Fa community where people are mixing
OL,15,Fclosely, such as a university, which
OL,16,Fcreates an environment where the
OL,17,Fbacteria can spread more easily.
OL,19,FWhat are the symptoms of meningitis?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/25
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
