OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773864688
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FIn most cases, meningitis is caused by
OL,7,Fa viral or bacterial infection. Viral
OL,8,Fmeningitis is more common and
OL,9,Ftypically less serious, often getting
OL,10,Fbetter within 7 to 10 days.
OL,12,FMeanwhile, bacterial meningitis is
OL,13,Frare but can be life-threatening.
OL,15,FUKHSA has said that some of the cases
OL,16,Flinked to the recent Kent meningitis
OL,17,Foutbreak are bacterial, caused by a
OL,18,Fstrain known as meningitis B, or menB.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/25
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31109
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773864688
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FDr Zina Alfahl, School of Medicine,
OL,7,FUniversity of Galway, says outbreaks
OL,8,Fare usually driven by a combination of
OL,9,Ffactors: "the characteristics of the
OL,10,Fstrain itself, the level of immunity
OL,11,Fin the population, and environmental
OL,12,Ffactors like crowded living or social
OL,13,Fsettings where people mix intensively".
OL,15,FUsually, the meningitis is spread by
OL,16,Fpeople who are not ill themselves, but
OL,17,Frather carry the viruses or bacteria
OL,18,Fin their nose or throat.
OL,20,FIn some cases, it can be spread by
OL,21,Fsomeone with meningitis.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/25
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31110
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773864688
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FThe UKHSA says that "very
OL,7,Foccasionally" meningococcal bacteria
OL,8,Fcan cause serious illness, including
OL,9,Finflammation of the lining of the
OL,10,Fbrain and blood poisoning, which can
OL,11,Frapidly lead to sepsis.
OL,13,FUnlike a common cold or flu, the
OL,14,Fdisease is passed on only through very
OL,15,Fclose contact, such as sharing food or
OL,16,Fdrink.
OL,18,FWhat can people do to protect
OL,19,Fthemselves from meningitis?
OL,26,@nD@UOUoD@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/25
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31111
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773864688
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FDr Alfahl says that the most
OL,7,F"important thing is recognising
OL,8,Fsymptoms early and seeking medical
OL,9,Fhelp quickly".
OL,11,FEarly symptoms can look like flu but
OL,12,Fpeople should seek urgent medical
OL,13,Fadvice if symptoms worsen or if there
OL,14,Fare warning signs such as neck
OL,15,Fstiffness, confusion, sensitivity to
OL,16,Flight, or a rash that doesn't fade
OL,17,Fwhen pressed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/25
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
