OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773864688
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FTom Nutt, chief executive of
OL,7,FMeningitis Now, says: "University
OL,8,Fstudents and young adults are among
OL,9,Fthe groups at increased risk because
OL,10,Fmeningitis bacteria can spread more
OL,11,Feasily in settings where people live,
OL,12,Fstudy and socialise closely together."
OL,14,FTrish Mannes, UKHSA regional deputy
OL,15,Fdirector for the South East, adds:
OL,16,F"Students are particularly at risk of
OL,17,Fmissing the early warning signs of
OL,18,Fmeningitis because they can be easily
OL,19,Fconfused with other illnesses such as
OL,20,Fa bad cold, flu or even a hangover.
OL,26,@xD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G23/25
